PORT RICHEY, Fla. -- The special election to replace former Mayor Eloise Taylor was held in Pasco County Tuesday night and ex-councilman Dale "Doc" Massad led all candidates with 40.72 percent of the votes. Pasco County Supervisor of Elections Brian Corley tweeted out a photo of the unofficial results at 7:16 p.m. Thx to my staff who did an outstanding job with today's special election! #Pascovotes pic.twitter.com/WziDsHOaOB â€” Brian Corley (@brianecorley) October 13, 2015 
448 votes were cast out of a total of 1,670 registered voters. 
PORT RICHEY MAYORAL SPECIAL ELECTION UNOFFICIAL RESULTS: Dale "Doc" Massad - 182 votes (40.72%) Bob Breedlove - 161 votes (36.02%) Kathy Todd - 104 (23.27%) 
The unofficial winner of the election has not been without controversy. After losing an election in 2004, he signed a petition to have the city disbanded . Massad also faced accusations in 2008 for sexually assaulting an ex-girlfriend . His handgun was also stolen from his pickup truck in 2009 and used by a man who committed suicide .
